verses.text_plain: My son, forget not my law; but let thine heart keep my commandments:
verses.verse_html: 1My son, forget not my law; but let thine heart keep my commandments:

verses.text_plain: For length of days, and long life, and peace, shall they add to thee.
verses.verse_html:
2For length of days, and long life, and peace, shall they add to thee. ▼
▼ long…: Heb. years of life

footnotes.body_html: ▼ long…: Heb. years of life

verses.text_plain: Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck; write them upon the table of thine heart:
verses.verse_html: 3Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck; write them upon the table of thine heart:

verses.text_plain: So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man.
verses.verse_html:
4So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man. ▼
▼ good…: or, good success

footnotes.body_html: ▼ good…: or, good success

verses.text_plain: Trust in the Lord with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding.
verses.verse_html: 5Trust in the Lord with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding.

verses.text_plain: In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.
verses.verse_html: 6In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.

verses.text_plain: Be not wise in thine own eyes: fear the Lord, and depart from evil.
verses.verse_html: 7Be not wise in thine own eyes: fear the Lord, and depart from evil.

verses.text_plain: It shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones.
verses.verse_html:
8It shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones. ▼
▼ health: Heb. medicine
 , ▼
▼ marrow: Heb. watering, or, moistening

footnotes.body_html: ▼ marrow: Heb. watering, or, moistening

verses.text_plain: Honour the Lord with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase:
verses.verse_html: 9Honour the Lord with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase:

verses.text_plain: So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.
verses.verse_html: 10So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.

verses.text_plain: My son, despise not the chastening of the Lord; neither be weary of his correction:
verses.verse_html: 11My son, despise not the chastening of the Lord; neither be weary of his correction:

verses.text_plain: For whom the Lord loveth he correcteth; even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.
verses.verse_html: 12For whom the Lord loveth he correcteth; even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.

verses.text_plain: Happy is the man that findeth wisdom, and the man that getteth understanding.
verses.verse_html:
13Happy is the man that findeth wisdom, and the man that getteth understanding. ▼
▼ that getteth…: Heb. that draweth out understanding

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that getteth…: Heb. that draweth out understanding
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that getteth…: Heb. that draweth out understanding

verses.text_plain: For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.
verses.verse_html: 14For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.

verses.text_plain: She is more precious than rubies: and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.
verses.verse_html: 15She is more precious than rubies: and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.

tokens.text: and all the things thou canst desire

verses.text_plain: Length of days is in her right hand; and in her left hand riches and honour.
verses.verse_html: 16Length of days is in her right hand; and in her left hand riches and honour.

verses.text_plain: Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.
verses.verse_html: 17Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.

verses.text_plain: She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy is every one that retaineth her.
verses.verse_html: 18She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy is every one that retaineth her.

verses.text_plain: The Lord by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens.
verses.verse_html:
19The Lord by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens. ▼
▼ established: or, prepared

verses.text_plain: By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.
verses.verse_html: 20By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.

verses.text_plain: My son, let not them depart from thine eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:
verses.verse_html: 21My son, let not them depart from thine eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:

verses.text_plain: So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.
verses.verse_html: 22So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.

verses.text_plain: Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.
verses.verse_html: 23Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.

verses.text_plain: When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid: yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.
verses.verse_html: 24When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid: yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.

verses.text_plain: Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.
verses.verse_html: 25Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.

verses.text_plain: For the Lord shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.
verses.verse_html: 26For the Lord shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.

verses.text_plain: Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do it.
verses.verse_html:
27Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do it. ▼
▼ them…: Heb. the owners thereof

tokens.text: from them to whom it is due
when it is in the power

footnotes.body_html: ▼ them…: Heb. the owners thereof

verses.text_plain: Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.
verses.verse_html: 28Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.

verses.text_plain: Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.
verses.verse_html:
29Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee. ▼
▼ Devise…: or, Practise no evil

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Devise…: or, Practise no evil

verses.text_plain: Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.
verses.verse_html: 30Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.

verses.text_plain: Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways.
verses.verse_html:
31Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways. ▼
▼ the oppressor: Heb. a man of violence

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the oppressor: Heb. a man of violence
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the oppressor: Heb. a man of violence

verses.text_plain: For the froward is abomination to the Lord: but his secret is with the righteous.
verses.verse_html: 32For the froward is abomination to the Lord: but his secret is with the righteous.

verses.text_plain: The curse of the Lord is in the house of the wicked: but he blesseth the habitation of the just.
verses.verse_html: 33The curse of the Lord is in the house of the wicked: but he blesseth the habitation of the just.

verses.text_plain: Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.
verses.verse_html: 34Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.

verses.text_plain: The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools.
verses.verse_html:
35The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools. ▼
▼ shall be…: Heb. exalteth the fools

footnotes.body_text: ▼ shall be…: Heb. exalteth the fools
footnotes.body_html: ▼ shall be…: Heb. exalteth the fools
